Title: New equations for vacuum correlators in gauge theories
Authors: D.V.Antonov (ITEP, Moscow)
Comments: 26 pages
Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A11 (1996) 4401-4418
\\
  Stochastic quantization is applied to derivation of equations connecting
multilocal gauge-invariant correlators in different field theories. They
include Abelian Higgs Model, QCD with spinless quarks at T=0 and T>0 and QED,
where spin effects are taken into account exactly.
